FBIS3-28276 "dreas024__a94010" FBIS-EAS-94-024-A Document Type:Daily Report 4 February 1994 ANNEX Japan SDPJ Chairman Opposes AWACS Purchase OW0202144094 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 2 Feb 94 Morning Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW0202144094 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN Language: Japanese Article Type:BFN [Text] While speaking at a 1 February news conference about a government plan to purchase Airborne Warning and Control System (AWACS) aircraft, Tomiichi Murayama, chairman of the Social Democratic Party of Japan [SDPJ], said: "Since the world has entered an age of disarmament, it is important for Japan -- which embraces a Constitution advocating the preservation of peace -- to exercise leadership. In particular, the plan to purchase AWACS aircarft should be shelved." The issue of the AWACS purchase has become one of the focal points in working out the draft national budget for fiscal 1994. Murayama thus indicated his opposition to appropriate funds in the draft budget for their procurement.
